# Project Context
Project Name: HandWrite AI
Description: A web application that converts typed text into highly realistic, generated handwriting on a folio paper background.

# Tech Stack & Environment
- Frontend: Next.js (App Router), React 18, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, Framer Motion, Lucide React.
- Backend: Python 3.12, Flask, Pillow (PIL), OpenCV (cv2), Google GenAI, Cloudinary.
- Database/Auth: Supabase.

# Strict Directory Structure Mapping
- `frontend/app/`: Next.js App Router pages, layouts, and `globals.css`.
- `frontend/public/fonts/`: Local UI fonts ONLY (e.g., Virgil.ttf) loaded via `next/font/local` in `layout.tsx`.
- `backend/app.py`: Main Flask entry point and API definitions.
- `backend/handwriting_*.py`: Core Python logic for image processing and rendering.
- `backend/fonts/`: TrueType fonts (.ttf) used exclusively by PIL to draw text on images. MUST NOT be imported by frontend CSS.
- `backend/uploads/`: Temporary local cache and folios.

